1
00:00:58,021 --> 00:01:00,997
=Within The Grip=

2
00:01:00,997 --> 00:01:02,967
=Episode 7=

3
00:01:02,967 --> 00:01:06,989
(You're Here to Kill Me)

4
00:01:10,239 --> 00:01:13,480
Gu Yuluo has a blade wound on her back,
likely from the past month.

5
00:01:14,359 --> 00:01:16,959
Investigate it carefully.

6
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:18,000
Yes.

7
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:21,120
Master, do you suspect it was her?

8
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:21,879
Dear.

9
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:36,519
What brings you here, honey?

10
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:44,040
I'm afraid that the tailor may hurt you.

11
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:48,239
You're still injured. I'm concerned.

12
00:01:49,159 --> 00:01:49,959
Let me do this.

13
00:03:00,479 --> 00:03:01,360
Thank you.

14
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,360
It's my duty.

15
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:18,479
I was worried Xuanji would discover
discrepancies in your measurements.

16
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:20,280
Seems I overthought it.

17
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:24,759
Yours are nearly identical.
No difference.

18
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:29,360
You even remember such trivial details.

19
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:32,800
It appears you and your husband
are truly deep in love.

20
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,240
You must be joking.

21
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:39,159
Didn't I mention days ago
I'd teach you chess?

22
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,719
Since we're free now,

23
00:03:42,879 --> 00:03:45,520
shall we play a few rounds?

24
00:03:57,199 --> 00:03:58,639
Indeed, you're no ordinary servant.

25
00:04:04,479 --> 00:04:05,280
Master.

26
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:29,199
You let me win.

27
00:04:31,639 --> 00:04:34,519
Your chess skill is exceptional.
I'm no match.

28
00:04:34,839 --> 00:04:37,480
In chess, the board

29
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:38,920
reveals the heart.

30
00:04:40,199 --> 00:04:42,240
Your mind wasn't on the game.

31
00:04:44,399 --> 00:04:47,079
You were holding back.

32
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:50,120
What troubles you?

33
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,879
May I share your burden?

34
00:04:54,319 --> 00:04:55,279
There is one thing.

35
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,040
Please tell.

36
00:05:03,639 --> 00:05:06,920
What was the Xuanji Pavilion
that Chaosheng mentioned yesterday?

37
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:24,519
How did you get that injury?

38
00:05:31,399 --> 00:05:33,839
In what capacity are you asking me that?

39
00:05:36,639 --> 00:05:38,160
Since you call me your husband,

40
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:40,920
how could I ignore your injury?

41
00:05:44,319 --> 00:05:47,240
Our trade routes
face inevitable trouble.

42
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:50,199
This minor injury means nothing.

43
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:56,240
- Why did Chaosheng visit last night?
- How would I know?

44
00:06:01,759 --> 00:06:02,560
And Xuanji?

45
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,519
Why did Xuanji come today?

46
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,519
Is she trustworthy?

47
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:13,639
If I said this was all for Zhaoxi,

48
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,519
would you believe me, Yuluo?

49
00:06:19,319 --> 00:06:21,600
Master, the Pavilion Master needs you.

50
00:06:38,879 --> 00:06:40,680
Everyone has secrets.

51
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,120
Regardless of our goals,

52
00:06:43,879 --> 00:06:44,959
we're allies for now.

53
00:06:47,639 --> 00:06:48,439
Dear.

54
00:06:49,199 --> 00:06:51,079
Best not to pry too deeply.

55
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,160
Master.

56
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,040
A new task?

57
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:25,759
No new tasks today.

58
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,959
Nor did I see you here today.

59
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,000
Aren't you curious

60
00:07:32,199 --> 00:07:35,800
about why I assigned you this task?

61
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:41,040
First rule for Xuanji Pavilion spies.

62
00:07:41,319 --> 00:07:43,120
Never question origins or motives.

63
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:45,240
Return intelligence intact.

64
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:49,079
That's the sharpest blade
the Pavilion requires.

65
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,480
Go.

66
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,160
Master, you're right.

67
00:08:28,759 --> 00:08:31,680
The Pavilion Master
initially assigned this task to Zhe Zhu.

68
00:08:32,279 --> 00:08:34,799
I heard she accepted the task.

69
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:37,480
But she couldn't execute it
due to a hand injury.

70
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,320
What do you make of this?

71
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,759
This task involves Prince Consort.

72
00:08:47,759 --> 00:08:49,399
We're only looking for leverage,

73
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:51,519
but it involves Princess Shang.

74
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:54,360
One wrong move,
and it may drag in too many people.

75
00:08:55,080 --> 00:09:00,240
Perhaps Zhe Zhu understood the stakes
and deliberately avoided it.

76
00:09:01,559 --> 00:09:02,559
Likely more than that.

77
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:06,039
Given Zhe Zhu's nature,

78
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:09,679
she wouldn't refuse a task
despite knowing the risks.

79
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:12,159
What made her abandon the task?

80
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:14,919
Even willingly sustain injuries?

81
00:09:15,399 --> 00:09:17,600
Only that person from Tianfeng Pavilion.

82
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:18,840
Master Chaosheng?

83
00:09:20,879 --> 00:09:23,799
But why would he make
Zhe Zhu abandon the task?

84
00:09:24,639 --> 00:09:26,240
The task explicitly mentions

85
00:09:27,039 --> 00:09:30,919
Prince Consort secretly seeks someone
to paint plum blossoms.

86
00:09:32,159 --> 00:09:35,080
But despite he scoured
renowned painters,

87
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:38,919
none could produce a painting
to his satisfaction.

88
00:09:39,919 --> 00:09:44,039
Instead, he gouged out
the eyes of the painters who failed.

89
00:09:45,159 --> 00:09:46,799
The Pavilion will seize this opportunity

90
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:50,639
to place an agent near the Consort.

91
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:52,799
But

92
00:09:53,639 --> 00:09:56,999
top-tier painters in the Xuanji Pavilion

93
00:09:56,999 --> 00:09:59,399
are only Zhe Zhu and me.

94
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,480
They intend to...

95
00:10:05,919 --> 00:10:08,879
No, Master!
You mustn't accept this task.

96
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:10,919
What's there to fear?

97
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,799
So many painters.

98
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:16,519
Why couldn't a single one
paint plum blossoms to his liking?

99
00:10:26,799 --> 00:10:30,519
Depart immediately for Qinyang,
the Consort's ancestral home.

100
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,399
You've been at the Pavilion so long.

101
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:52,039
You should know
we don't get to choose our tasks.

102
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:55,600
After joining the Pavilion,

103
00:10:56,159 --> 00:10:58,639
when did we have the luxury
of following our hearts?

104
00:10:59,679 --> 00:11:04,320
We are merely controlled puppets
and blades without emotion.

105
00:11:08,039 --> 00:11:09,000
Understood, Master.

106
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:12,399
At least staying by your side

107
00:11:13,279 --> 00:11:14,440
was my own choice.

108
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:07,519
Miss Li, my master
is waiting on the second floor.

109
00:12:07,919 --> 00:12:09,840
You must have received the deposit.

110
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:12,879
Whether you finish the painting or not,
there's no need for a refund.

111
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:18,759
But, regarding my master's identity,
I hope you won't inquire further.

112
00:12:29,759 --> 00:12:32,559
Master, the second floor
of the teahouse is booked for tonight.

113
00:12:32,759 --> 00:12:35,720
I thought that might be the person
she's meeting, so I investigated.

114
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:38,240
That's Prince Consort.

115
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:40,600
He hasn't picked a side at court.

116
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:43,279
The Right Chancellor
and the General tried to court him.

117
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:46,480
But you once had me
investigate him covertly.

118
00:12:46,879 --> 00:12:50,120
Neither the Consort
nor the Princess has clean hands.

119
00:12:52,399 --> 00:12:54,639
The one at the entrance
is the Princess's maid.

120
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:58,919
Strangely, he has secretly sought people
to draw plum blossoms for him.

121
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:02,600
None of the renowned painters
he invited could satisfy him.

122
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:04,759
Finally, he gouged out all their eyes.

123
00:13:05,639 --> 00:13:09,799
Princess Shang is usually cautious.
Why is she indulging his madness now?

124
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:34,360
Master, this is Miss Li,
the painter from Lanling.

125
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:38,039
Sit down.

126
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:03,679
There are no plum blossoms here.

127
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:09,120
I've heard skilled painters can paint
based on descriptions alone.

128
00:14:09,759 --> 00:14:13,600
That wouldn't be difficult for you?

129
00:14:14,799 --> 00:14:16,879
(I've heard of
portraiture by description.)

130
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:21,399
(But painting flowers this way?
It won't be that simple.)

131
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,919
(No wonder those painters...)

132
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,240
Please tell.

133
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,879
I often have a dream.

134
00:14:29,559 --> 00:14:32,120
In the dream, when snow
blankets the courtyard,

135
00:14:33,039 --> 00:14:34,919
plum blossoms drift down one by one.

136
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:38,759
Red silk ribbons cling
among the flowers.

137
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:43,320
Are you alright, sir?

138
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:44,759
It's nothing.

139
00:14:45,639 --> 00:14:47,399
I've had these headaches for years.

140
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:51,879
Fortunately, this incense
provides temporary relief.

141
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,799
But sometimes, I can't distinguish

142
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:56,600
between reality

143
00:14:59,039 --> 00:15:00,679
and dreams.

144
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:04,440
Constant incense burning
will harm your health eventually.

145
00:15:04,879 --> 00:15:06,600
You don't mind if I open the window?

146
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:07,360
Not at all.

147
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:28,720
You may begin painting.

148
00:15:43,919 --> 00:15:44,720
(Xuan Qing.)

149
00:15:45,559 --> 00:15:47,159
(Can you return in time?)

150
00:16:13,039 --> 00:16:13,840
After her!

151
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:25,919
How's the painting going?

152
00:16:26,639 --> 00:16:27,720
Not a single stroke yet.

153
00:16:29,639 --> 00:16:31,000
Of course she can't paint it.

154
00:16:31,799 --> 00:16:35,480
Because she's not the painter Miss Li.

155
00:16:35,879 --> 00:16:37,759
She's an assassin here to kill you.

156
00:16:56,679 --> 00:16:58,200
You're here to kill me?

157
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:01,200
I'm merely a painter.

158
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:04,680
I don't know
why you'd frame me for murder.

159
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:09,799
So you're not.

160
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:11,960
How dull.

161
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:14,720
Since you're not here to kill me,

162
00:17:15,759 --> 00:17:16,839
kill her.

163
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:19,720
Master.

164
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,039
Wait!

165
00:17:23,039 --> 00:17:25,160
I can paint the plum blossoms you want.

166
00:17:34,039 --> 00:17:37,039
Do you know how many painters
claimed they could do it?

167
00:17:37,759 --> 00:17:39,880
But none succeeded in the end.

168
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,759
Care to guess their fate?

169
00:17:44,079 --> 00:17:45,359
I can paint it.

170
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:47,480
Good.

171
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:33,000
Don't forget. Our master
wants a plum blossom painting.

172
00:18:33,519 --> 00:18:36,880
You've painted bare branches.
Where are the blossoms?

173
00:18:40,279 --> 00:18:43,240
But despite he scoured
renowned painters,

174
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:46,720
none could produce a painting
to his satisfaction.

175
00:18:47,599 --> 00:18:49,240
I often have a dream.

176
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:52,279
In the dream, when snow
blankets the courtyard,

177
00:18:52,759 --> 00:18:54,519
plum blossoms drift down one by one.

178
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:58,279
Red silk ribbons cling
among the flowers.

179
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,319
You're here to kill me?

180
00:19:06,039 --> 00:19:08,480
What? Giving up already?

181
00:19:41,599 --> 00:19:45,160
I thought you had skill, but now,
you defile this painting with blood.

182
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:48,119
It just seems a performance
to attract attention.

183
00:19:54,759 --> 00:19:58,799
Are these the snow-covered plum blossoms
from your dreams?

184
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:38,423
♪Willows sway in the twilight breeze♪

185
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:44,281
♪Ancient alleys guard time's secrets♪

186
00:20:44,848 --> 00:20:51,476
♪Bluestones bear life's imprints♪

187
00:20:51,476 --> 00:20:56,240
♪Falling petals, endless longing♪

188
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:58,576
♪Longing lingers within my heart♪

189
00:20:58,576 --> 00:21:05,276
♪Zither strings sigh
for the sorrow parting♪

190
00:21:05,276 --> 00:21:12,048
♪Past tales nest in my soul♪

191
00:21:12,048 --> 00:21:19,184
♪Affection lingers, unforgettable♪

192
00:21:19,184 --> 00:21:23,568
♪Ink-stained scrolls recall bygones♪

193
00:21:23,568 --> 00:21:26,192
♪Each stroke holds a thought♪

194
00:21:26,192 --> 00:21:32,826
♪Prosperity fades like dreams♪

195
00:21:32,826 --> 00:21:39,376
♪Past tales nest in my soul♪

196
00:21:39,376 --> 00:21:46,500
♪Affection lingers, unforgettable♪

197
00:21:46,590 --> 00:21:50,960
♪Ink-stained scrolls recall bygones♪

198
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:53,668
♪Each stroke holds a thought♪

199
00:21:53,668 --> 00:21:59,568
♪Prosperity fades like dreams♪

200
00:22:00,208 --> 00:22:06,196
♪Past tales nest in my soul♪

